<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101275124650051></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101275124650051><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=141146&mid=101275124650051>adventure in a new land</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=141146&mid=101275124650051#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=141146><span id= >Igon</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>4 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Feb 3rd 11:49 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I crossed the Ocean of Tears and landed at a place called Freeport. It was a busy place, full of merchants and travelers. Humans were much more common in this land than Faydwer, as were, I was told, ogres, trolls and dark elves. I made a note to myself to travel to their lands in the future.<br>I went into a tavern. I bought some ale and asked the bartender where I could find adventure on this continent. He suggested the plains of Karana. He mentioned that the southern plains were especially dangerous, with cities of gnolls and aviaks.<br>From the very beginning of my career, my guild had put a bounty on the aviaks who roamed Butcherblock. Hearing that my old foes also brought terror to this continent, my destination was clear. I began the long trek to Southern Karana.<br>I passed through the common lands and a place called Kithicor Forest. It was inhabited by undead monstrosities, so I spent some time battling those creatures.<br>I then journeyed to Highhold. As I was leaving that place, I was attacked by a group of gnolls. I had several encounters with gnolls while in Steamfont. I didn't like them. I destroyed the group that assaulted me and then continued on my journey.<br>The run along the shoreline was long and uneventful. The bridge to Southern Karana was a sight for sore eyes. True action was now close at hand.<br>*to be continued*<br>&nbsp;<br>Gawayne Paendrag - 24th Dwarven Paladin of Brell Serillis - Bristlebane server</td></tr>
